The figure shows three concentric circles with four lines passing through their common centre. What percentage of the figure is shaded?

\begin{aligned} &\text{The area of the shaded region} = \pi r^2 - \pi r_2^2 - \pi r_3^2 \\\\ &= \pi(6^2) - \pi(4^2) - \pi(2^2) \\\\ &= 36\pi - 16\pi - 4\pi \\\\ &= 16\pi \end{aligned}

\begin{aligned} &\text{The total area of the figure} = \pi r^2 + \pi r_2^2 + \pi r_3^2 \\\\ &= \pi(6^2) + \pi(4^2) + \pi(2^2) \\\\ &= 36\pi + 16\pi + 4\pi \\\\ &= 56\pi \end{aligned}

\begin{aligned} &\text{The percentage of the figure that is shaded} = \frac{\text{area of shaded region}}{\text{total area}} \\\\ &= \frac{16\pi}{56\pi} \\\\ &= \frac{16}{56} \\\\ &= \frac{2}{7} \\\\ &\approx \boxed{29\%} \end{aligned}

