As the disk rolls around the clock, it will travel a distance equal to its circumference, which is $2\pi(10)=20\pi$. During this time, the arrow on the disk will rotate a full $360^\circ$ plus however much it rotates as the disk travels its own diameter. Since the arrow starts and ends in the vertical position, it must rotate an additional $180^\circ$, for a total rotation of $540^\circ$.
